text: Lukita Maxwell (born October 27, 2001) is an Indonesian-born American actress. She is known for her television roles as Delilah in the HBO Max series Generation (2021) and as Alice in the Apple TV+ series Shrinking (2023). Maxwell was born in Jakarta, Indonesia to a Chinese-Indonesian mother and a white American father. She spent her early childhood in Bali before moving to the United States in St. George, Utah.
